The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 6: The governments direct tax collections grew just 3.69 per cent in the first half of the fiscal to Rs 1.52 lakh crore because of higher refunds. Experts said lower outgo towards refunds in the later part and revival in the economy would help the government achieve its full-year target of 7.24 per cent growth in direct tax mop-up.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 6: The Essar Groups Rs 4,500-crore non-convertible debentures issue was oversubscribed within a few hours of opening yesterday. The issue is likely to close on October 21 or even earlier, sources said. NCDs are private company bonds that cannot be converted into shares.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 6: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee has decided to hold zonal meetings with PSU banks of the east zone in Calcutta on October 24. The minster usually meets the heads of banks in the capital. He will review the performance of the banks headquartered in the region.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 6: Loans from regional rural banks to micro and small enterprises will now be considered as priority sector lending. The loans provide certain services such as education and housing.                             
	 Calcutta, Oct. 6: Coal India Limited has recorded a 20 per cent dip in profit before tax in the first half of the current fiscal because of a wage and salary revision. PBT rose to Rs 3,600 crore (provisional) in the first six months of 2009-10 compared with Rs 4,484 crore in the same period last year.                                                                                                                           
